    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>London</placeName>
                    <date>11 November 1858</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>Thanks for your M. <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ralfs’ Case, which D. <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Hooker had been so good as to send me &amp; I have told him I will subscribe 5 guineas towards the fund to be raised for him. His fate is truly affecting &amp; I hope &amp; trust the small sum required to <del>raise</del> provide the annual pittances to keep him from starvation will be forthcoming.</p>
                  <p>I was very glad to see from the Times yesterday that so many young Botanists have passed a satisfactory examination at Cambridge. This looks well for the progress of Natural History with you.</p>
                  <p>I am | my dear Sir |yours very truly |W. Spence</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
